(a) TWO (2) years of experience working in a Security Operation Center with security monitoring and escalation of threats responsibilities;

(b) Relevant training on the proposed products, and has obtained professional certification such as GIAC Information Assurance Certified Intrusion Analyst (GCIA), GIAC Information Assurance Certified Incident Handler (GCIH), or equivalent.

(a) Providing continuous technical monitoring (such as intrusion identification, event correlation and threat containment), detection, correlation, analysis and support involving handling of cyber event such as identifying user security issues;

(b) Performing initial analysis (e.g. analysing and reviewing alerts, eliminating false positives and determining severity of threats) to determine impact of compromise;

(c) Determining the nature, mechanisms and scope of incident by performing event correlation and historical searches to determine the extent of a security compromise;

(d) Performing event correlation... across the In-Scope Institutions to identify similar attack pattern and spread of attack;

(e) Handling case management, generating tickets and reports when required, and tracking open tickets until closure;

(f) Generating incident or investigative reports
